COMPONENT NAME: LKM SQL to DB2 UDB (LOAD)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from any ANSI SQL-92 compliant database to a DB2 UDB database using the native LOAD command. - This module extracts data in a temporary file. The data is then loaded into the temporary DB2 table created dynamically using the LOAD CLP command.
Restrictions: - The IBM DB2 Command Line Processor (CLP) as well as the IBM DB2 Connect Software must be installed on the machine running the ODI Agent. - The IBM DB2 Command Line Processor (CLP) need the server name to be set in the topology - The user specified in the IBM DB2 Data Server in the ODI Topology must have enough privileges to run the LOAD utility (this can be achieved with a GRANT LOAD ON DATABASE statement). - The temporary data file format is delimited by tabs (Hexadecimal character 0x09) - Specify appropriate options values according to their description. - DB2 user profile (bash) such as $INSTHOME/sqllib/db2profile must be available for specifying DB2_PROFILE option. This is important to configure the CLP runtime environment. - Use KM options DATA_FILE_PERMISSION to grant (chmod) READ permission on loading data file. E.g. "a+r" if CLP is not in the same group. - Use KM options EXECUTION_PERMISION to grant (chmod) EXECUTE permission Grant (chmod) on loading script. E.g. "a+x" if CLP is not in the same group.
Note : The timestamp format is a combination of the date format and the time format
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

Additional options used when creating the C$ temporary table. You may use this option if you wish to create the temporary table in a nologging mode (transaction is not written to the DB2 log files) or if you wish to specify a tablespace name. Examples: - Disable logging: NOT LOGGED INITIALLY - Specify a tablespace: IN MY_TABLESPACE NOT LOGGED INITIALLY - Compress Values: VALUE COMPRESSION
Temp. Directory for the data file

Directory where the temporary data file is created. This directory must be a valid path on the machine running the Sunopsis Agent. Examples: - On Windows: D:\MyDatafiles\MyTemporaryFolder - On Unix / Linux: /usr/tmp

Specify the date format according to the DB2 LOAD utility documentation. Example: YYYY-MM-DD
Note : this format will be used as date format to unload source data into the temporary file for all date columns.

Specify the date format according to the DB2 LOAD utility documentation. Example: HH:MM:SS
Note : this format will be used as time format to unload source data into the temporary file for all time columns.
Path to DB2 UDB user profile (e.g. $INSTHOME/sqllib/db2profile from installed home)
Grant (chmod) READ permission on loading data file. E.g. "a+r" if CLP is not in the same group.
Grant (chmod) EXECUTE permission on loading script. E.g. "a+x" if CLP is not in the same group.
